article.headline: Oklahoma 90, Montana State 59
article.story:
BOZEMAN, Mont. (AP) -- Caton Hill scored a season-high 23 points
and pulled down 10 rebounds Wednesday night to lead No. 14 Oklahoma
to a 90-59 victory over Montana State.

Lauren Shoush added a career-high 18 points and Maria Villarroel
had 15 for the Sooners (7-0), who led by 27 points at halftime.

Oklahoma hit a season-high 11 3-pointers, including four each by
Hill and Shoush.

The Bobcats (5-3) cut the lead to 50-36 on a 3-pointer by
Hillary Scott with 14:48 left but did not get any closer.

Kati Burrows led Montana State with 15 points.

The Sooners opened the game with four consecutive 3-pointers and
hit eight in the first half in taking the 52-25 lead.
